(self.webpackChunkdiva_docs=self.webpackChunkdiva_docs||[]).push([[562],{3650:(e,a,t)=>{"use strict";t.r(a),t.d(a,{data:()=>i});const i={key:"v-6d8df22a",path:"/user-docs/details/profiling-metadata.html",title:"Profiling Metadata",lang:"en-US",frontmatter:{},excerpt:"",headers:[{level:2,title:"Text Files",slug:"text-files",children:[]},{level:2,title:"Table Files",slug:"table-files",children:[]},{level:2,title:"Image Files",slug:"image-files",children:[]}],filePathRelative:"user-docs/details/profiling-metadata.md",git:{contributors:[]}}},8923:(e,a,t)=>{"use strict";t.r(a),t.d(a,{default:()=>h});var i=t(6252);const l=(0,i.uE)('<h1 id="profiling-metadata"><a class="header-anchor" href="#profiling-metadata">#</a> Profiling Metadata</h1><p>Currently we support automatic analysis of <strong>5</strong> different file types. The metadata is only populated by our automatic profiling and cannot be edited. This is because we want to preserve the objective analysis by a computer system here.</p><h2 id="text-files"><a class="header-anchor" href="#text-files">#</a> Text Files</h2><ul><li><code>application/pdf</code></li><li><code>text/plain</code></li></ul><p>The automatic analyses are listed and explained below:</p><ul><li>A set of simple metadata is extracted from the text file (size, PDF version, creation date, ...)</li><li>We are trying to determine the language of the text. A score is additionally stored, which indicates the confidence.</li><li>Keywords are extracted automatically. These are displayed on the main page of the entity.</li><li>Key phrases are extracted using two algorithms. Currently, these are <strong>LSA</strong> and <strong>Luhn</strong>.</li><li>A simple statistical evaluation on the distribution of charcters and number of different tokens (words, sentences, and characters).</li><li>We perform a scan for personal data and give a score between 0 and 100, where 100 means that the resource is very likely to be GDPR relevant.</li></ul>',6),s={class:"flex justify-center"},r=(0,i.uE)('<h2 id="table-files"><a class="header-anchor" href="#table-files">#</a> Table Files</h2><ul><li><code>text/csv</code></li><li><code>application/x-sas-data</code></li></ul><p>The automatic analyses are listed and explained below:</p><ul><li>We extract the schema of the table and visualize it.</li><li>We perform a statistical analysis that looks at each column and extracts key metrics.</li><li>We extract a sample set of the table to give an insight into the data.</li></ul>',4),n={class:"flex justify-center"},o={class:"flex justify-center"},c=(0,i.uE)('<h2 id="image-files"><a class="header-anchor" href="#image-files">#</a> Image Files</h2><ul><li><code>image/jpeg</code></li></ul><p>The automatic analyses are listed and explained below:</p><ul><li>We create a thumbnail so that you can see which image we are dealing with.</li><li>We try to recognize the objects seen in the picture.</li><li>We try to generate a caption for the image.</li><li>We perform OCR text recognition on the image to make text on images search relevant in our catalog as well.</li><li>We extract EXIF metadata, e.g. about the camera with which the photo was taken.</li></ul>',4),d={class:"flex justify-center"},h={render:function(e,a){return(0,i.wg)(),(0,i.j4)(i.HY,null,[l,(0,i.Wm)("div",s,[(0,i.Wm)("img",{class:"rounded-lg",src:e.$withBase("/assets/screenshots/details/profiling_text.png"),alt:"DIVA Text Profiling"},null,8,["src"])]),r,(0,i.Wm)("div",n,[(0,i.Wm)("img",{class:"rounded-lg",src:e.$withBase("/assets/screenshots/details/profiling_tabledata.png"),alt:"DIVA Table Data Profiling"},null,8,["src"])]),(0,i.Wm)("div",o,[(0,i.Wm)("img",{class:"rounded-lg",src:e.$withBase("/assets/screenshots/details/tabledata_sample.png"),alt:"DIVA Table Data Sample"},null,8,["src"])]),c,(0,i.Wm)("div",d,[(0,i.Wm)("img",{class:"rounded-lg",src:e.$withBase("/assets/screenshots/details/profiling_images.png"),alt:"DIVA Image Profiling"},null,8,["src"])])],64)}}}}]);